config MTHP_BESTFIT
	tristate "VMA-size best-fit mTHP order selection (Android vendor hook)"
	depends on TRANSPARENT_HUGEPAGE
	depends on ANDROID_VENDOR_HOOKS
	default m
	help
	  Loadable module that attaches to android_vh_thp_vma_allowable_orders
	  and caps the allowable mTHP order bitmask based on the faulting
	  VMA's size, min_pages configuration, and a contPTE bias policy.

	  ZERO changes to mm/memory.c or any GKI-locked file. The vendor
	  hook is stable across Android kernel releases (added in
	  android15-6.6, present in later branches including 6.12).

	    insmod: hook attached, faults get VMA-size filtering
	    rmmod:  hook removed, vanilla behavior restored

	  Runtime tunables:
	    /proc/sys/vm/mthp_bestfit/{enabled,min_pages,contpte_bias}
	    /sys/kernel/debug/mthp_bestfit/{stats,live,enabled}

	  If unsure, say M.
